description: Mentioned only by Audsley in his entry for Jula, which reads: The name given, according to Schlimbach and Seidel, to the Spitzflöte, 8 ft., but for what reason neither authority gives any information. The term Julaquinte has, after the same fashion, been used to designate a similar stop of either 5-1/3' or 2-2/3' pitch.
